  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      &progname; <arg>-n <replaceable>nick</replaceable></arg>
	<arg>-cmdt</arg> <arg plain><replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      &progname; <arg plain></arg><arg plain>-cr</arg>
	<arg>-n <replaceable>nick</replaceable></arg> <arg>-dm</arg>
	<arg>-g <replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      &progname; <arg>-h&brvbar;v</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>&package; was created first as a IRC (Internet Relay Chat) network
bot, i.e. the network daemon which controls functionality and protection
of IRC channels. It enters to IRC network as user, joins the channel and
tries don't leave it until crash or terminate. But now it is multipurpose
modularised client for networks: IRC, ICQ, etc.</para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1><title>OPTIONS</title>
.PD 1
Runs the bot with config file <it/file/ until <bf/-r/ option present.
.TP 10
<bf/-c/
Don't detach console (chat simulation mode).
.TP
<bf/-d/
Increase a debug log level by one (maximum debug level is 5).
.TP
<bf/-g/ <it/file/
Generate new config file <it/file/
.TP
<bf/-h/
Display help message and exit.
.TP
<bf/-m/
Make an empty listfile.
.TP
<bf/-n/ <it/nick/
Set default nick to <it/nick/
.TP
<bf/-r/
Reset parameters (don't use the config file statements).
.TP
<bf/-t/
Test the configuration and exit.
.TP
<bf/-v/
Display version information and exit.
.PD 0
